org.apache.juneau.http

Class NameValuePairSupplier

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.juneau.http.NameValuePairSupplier
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<NameValuePair>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NameValuePairSupplier.Null

    public class NameValuePairSupplier
extends Object
implements Iterable<NameValuePair>
    Specifies a dynamic supplier of NameValuePair objects. This class is thread safe.

      • add

        public NameValuePairSupplier add(String name,
                                 Supplier<?> value)
        Appends the specified name/value pair to the end of this list using a value supplier.

        The pair is added as a BasicNameValuePair.

        Value is re-evaluated on each call to BasicNameValuePair.getValue().

        Parameters:
        name - The pair name.
        value - The pair value supplier.
        Returns:
        This object (for method chaining).

      • add

        public NameValuePairSupplier add(String name,
                                 Object value,
                                 HttpPartType partType,
                                 HttpPartSerializerSession serializer,
                                 HttpPartSchema schema,
                                 boolean skipIfEmpty)
        Appends the specified name/value pair to the end of this list.

        The value is converted to UON notation using the UrlEncodingSerializer defined on the client.

        Parameters:
        name - The pair name.
        value - The pair value.
        partType - The HTTP part type.
        serializer - The serializer to use for serializing the value to a string value.
        schema - The schema object that defines the format of the output.
        If null, defaults to the schema defined on the parser.
        If that's also null, defaults to HttpPartSchema.DEFAULT.
        Only used if serializer is schema-aware (e.g. OpenApiSerializer).
        skipIfEmpty - If value is a blank string, the value should return as null.
        Returns:
        This object (for method chaining).
